<HEADLINE>
GERMAN GROUP TO TRAIN TAIPEI CLOWNS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Feb. 7. (CNA) 02/07/07  21:37:47 (By Y.L. Kao)
</P>
<P>
The German clown group Cirque Artikuss will present their skills
Feb. 14 at a clown workshop for children to be held in Taipei, a
spokesman for the event organizers said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by various Taiwanese enterprises, the German Cultural
Center in Taipei decided to organize the workshop and invite the
group with the aim of provoking children's imagination and giving
them a happy winter break, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The workshop will begin with a clown show that will be the
group's first performance in Taiwan, followed by a practice
session headed by Olav Keith and Andreas Landersheim, both of
whom are graduates of a comedy school in Hanover, according to
the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The children will be shown some basic clowning skills, including
warm-up activities,  circus performances,  juggling  and stunt
techniques.
</P>
